For this construct:

class A {
}
class B extends A {
}

the graaljs parser generates the default constructor:

constructor(...args) {
  super(...args);
}

This irritates the semicolon hint, as the token for the semicolon can't
be found and thus the hint is generated.

Closes: #4214

#4066

